The paper focuses on using reinforcement learning for robotic manipulation tasks, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of simulated locomotion demonstrations and physically-realistic simulators suggests a strong emphasis on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the proposed approach on complex tasks like multi-object stacking and non-rigid object manipulation suggests a potential focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
